getValueMap

public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getValueMap()
Description copied from interface: CloneAttributeData
Get a map with datatypeField name as a key, data is a String or a list of Map

For example:
Class Act {
...
SET<CS> statusCode
...
}

Class CS {
...
ST code()
UID codeSystem()
ST extension()
SET translation()
...
}

So this method creates a list with
map.put<"code", codeValue>,
map.put<"codeSystem", codeSystemValue>
map.put<"translation", anotherListOfMapOfCD>
This is simple data map protocal, which later will be used to converted into HL7 v3 data type

Specified by:
getValueMap in interface CloneAttributeData
Returns:
Map<String, Object>
